Wang Yi, director of the Office of the Foreign Affairs Commission of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, on Friday stressed China will continue to be the main engine of the world economy. During his meeting with Italian President Sergio Mattarella, the visiting senior Chinese diplomat stressed the COVID-19 epidemic in China has been brought under control and the Chinese economic outlook is becoming more promising by the day, which will also bring new opportunities for Sino-Italian cooperation. Wang, also a member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, urged the two sides to fully restart contact at all levels and promote mutually beneficial cooperation in various fields. As natural partners in building the Belt and Road Initiative, China and Italy can further explore the potential to inject strong momentum into the development of their relations, he added. (Cover: Wang Yi, director of the Office of the Foreign Affairs Commission of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, meets with Italian President Sergio Mattarella in Rome, Italy, February 17, 2023. /Chinese Foreign Ministry)